    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small ladies' work tables. In their classic form, may have galleries around its top and the shelf joining its legs to provide shallow receptacles into which one could place chiffons (scraps of ribbon and cloth) and other needlework materials; either square or circular in form and generally having three drawers, the uppermost sometimes fitted with writing equipment.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pequeñas mesas de trabajo para señoras en su forma clásica con galerías alrededor de su cubierta y el estante une sus patas para proporcionar receptáculos poco profundos en los que se pueden colocar chiffons (restos de cinta y tela) y otros materiales de costura; en forma cuadrada o circular y que generalmente tienen tres cajones, el superior algunas veces acondicionado con equipamiento de escritura.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleine dameswerktafels in de klassieke uitvoering, met randen rondom het tafelblad en rondom de plank die de poten verbindt, zodat hier ondiepe 'bakjes' ontstonden waar chiffons (reepjes lint en stof) en ander naaiwerk kon worden bewaard. Ze waren vierkant of rond en hadden meestal drie laden, waarvan de bovenste soms met schrijfgerei was uitgerust.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>女士專用的小型工作檯，樣式古典，桌面邊緣有裝飾，桌腳連接處有淺盤櫃架，可供放置絲帶、布料，以及其他女紅材料等。形式有矩形或圓形，一般有三個抽屜，最上層有時附有寫字工具。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tavoli da lavoro da donna di piccole dimensioni nella loro forma classica con gallerie intorno alla parte superiore e la mensola che unisce le gambe per fornire contenitori poco profondi in cui si possono collocare i chiffon (frammenti di nastro e stoffa) e altri materiali di cucito; di forma quadrata o circolare e generalmente con tre cassetti, il più alto a volte usato per attrezzatura per la scrittura.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109543/Italian Term Processing (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleiner Damen-Arbeitstisch in seiner klassischen Form mit einer Galerie um die Platte und einem Regalboden, der seine Beine verbindet, für flache Behälter zur Aufbewahrung von Chiffons (Band und Stoff) und andere Handarbeitsmaterialien; entweder quadratisch oder rund in der Form und im Allgemeinen mit drei Schubladen, die oberste manchmal ausgestattet mit Schreibzeug.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
